    {
      "id": "ASCE7-22-26.10-B3",
      "type": "body",
      "section": "26.10",
      "text": "The velocity pressure at mean roof height is computed as qh = qz evaluated from Equation (26.10-1) using Kz at mean roof height h. The basic wind speed, V, used in determination of design wind loads on rooftop structures, rooftop equipment, and other building appurtenances shall consider the Risk Category equal to the greater of the following:",
      "cross_references": [
        "26.10.1"
      ],
      "bbox": {
        "x_start": 0.06,
        "x_end": 0.48,
        "y_start": 0.1,
        "y_end": 0.18
      },
      "column": "left",
      "metadata": {
        "extracted_by": "vision-clone",
        "qc_status": "pending"
      },
      "_source": "left"
    },
    {
      "id": "ASCE7-22-26.10-B4",
      "type": "body",
      "section": "26.10",
      "text": "1. Risk category for the building on which the equipment or appurtenance is located, or\n2. Risk category for any building or other structure to which the equipment or appurtenance provides a necessary service.",
