    {
      "id": "ASCE7-22-26.11.1-H2",
      "type": "body",
      "section": "26.11.1",
      "text": "26.11.1 Gust-Effect Factor The gust-effect factor for a rigid building or other structure is permitted to be taken as 0.85.",
      "cross_references": [],
      "bbox": {
        "x_start": 0.06,
        "x_end": 0.48,
        "y_start": 0.25,
        "y_end": 0.27
      },
      "column": "left",
      "heading": false,
      "metadata": {
        "extracted_by": "vision-clone",
        "qc_status": "pending"
      },
      "_source": "left"
    },
    {
      "id": "ASCE7-22-26.11.2-H3",
      "type": "body",
      "section": "26.11.2",
      "text": "26.11.2 Frequency Determination To determine whether a building or other structure is rigid or fl exible as de fi ned in Section 26.2, the fundamental natural frequency, n 1 , shall be established using the structural properties and deformational characteristics of the resisting elements in a properly substantiated analysis. Low-rise buildings, as de fi ned in Section 26.2, are permitted to be considered rigid.",
      "cross_references": [],
      "bbox": {
        "x_start": 0.06,
        "x_end": 0.48,
        "y_start": 0.27,
        "y_end": 0.32
      },
      "column": "left",
      "heading": true,
      "metadata": {
        "extracted_by": "vision-clone",
        "qc_status": "pending"
      },
      "_source": "left"
    },
    {
      "id": "ASCE7-22-26.11.2-H3-body",
      "type": "body",
      "section": "26.11.2",
      "text": "whether a building or other structure is rigid or flexible as defined in Section 26.2, the fundamental natural frequency, n1, shall be established using the structural properties and deformational characteristics of the resisting elements in a properly substantiated analysis. Low-rise buildings, as defined in Section 26.2, are considered rigid.",
      "cross_references": [
        "26.2"
      ],
      "bbox": {
        "x_start": 0.06,
        "x_end": 0.48,
        "y_start": 0.28,
        "y_end": 0.32
      },
      "column": "left",
      "metadata": {
        "extracted_by": "vision-clone",
        "qc_status": "pending"
      },
      "_source": "left"
    },
    {
      "id": "ASCE7-22-26.11.2.1-H4-body",
      "type": "body",
      "section": "26.11.2.1",
      "text": "Frequency As an alternative to performing an analysis to determine n1, the approximate building natural frequency, na, shall be permitted to be calculated in accordance with Section 26.11.3 for structural steel, concrete, or masonry buildings meeting the following requirements:",
      "cross_references": [
        "26.11.3"
      ],
      "bbox": {
        "x_start": 0.06,
        "x_end": 0.48,
        "y_start": 0.33,
        "y_end": 0.37
      },
      "column": "left",
      "metadata": {
        "extracted_by": "vision-clone",
        "qc_status": "pending"
      },
      "_source": "left"
    },
    {
      "id": "ASCE7-22-26.11.2.1-B5",
      "type": "body",
      "section": "26.11.2.1",
      "text": "1. The building height is less than or equal to 300 ft (91 m).\n2. The building height is less than four times its effective length, Leff.",
      "cross_references": [],
      "bbox": {
        "x_start": 0.06,
        "x_end": 0.48,
        "y_start": 0.37,
        "y_end": 0.4
      },
      "column": "left",
      "metadata": {
        "extracted_by": "vision-clone",
        "qc_status": "pending"
      },
      "_source": "left"
    },
    {
      "id": "ASCE7-22-26.11.2.1-B6",
      "type": "body",
      "section": "26.11.2.1",
      "text": "The effective length, Leff, in the direction under consideration shall be determined from the following equation:",
      "cross_references": [],
      "bbox": {
        "x_start": 0.06,
        "x_end": 0.48,
        "y_start": 0.4,
        "y_end": 0.42
      },
      "column": "left",
      "metadata": {
        "extracted_by": "vision-clone",
        "qc_status": "pending"
      },
      "_source": "left"
    },
    {
      "id": "ASCE7-22-26.11-F3",
      "type": "formula",
      "section": "26.11",
      "text": "Leff = Σ(hiLi)/Σhi",
      "cross_references": [],
      "bbox": {
        "x_start": 0.06,
        "x_end": 0.48,
        "y_start": 0.43,
        "y_end": 0.46
      },
      "column": "left",
      "expression": "L_{eff} = \\frac{\\sum_{i=1}^{n} h_i L_i}{\\sum_{i=1}^{n} h_i}",
      "parameters": [
        "L_{eff} = effective length in the direction under consideration",
        "h_i = height above grade of level i",
        "L_i = building length at level i parallel to the wind direction"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "extracted_by": "vision-clone",
        "qc_status": "pending"
      },
      "_source": "left"
    },
    {
      "id": "ASCE7-22-26.10-note1",
      "type": "body",
      "section": "26.10",
      "text": "ᵃ Use 0.70 in Chapter 28, Exposure B, when z < 30 ft (9.1 m).\nNotes:\n1. Velocity pressure exposure coefficient Kz may be determined from the following formula:",
      "cross_references": [],
      "bbox": {
        "x_start": 0.532,
        "x_end": 0.938,
        "y_start": 0.435,
        "y_end": 0.488
      },
      "column": "right",
      "metadata": {
        "extracted_by": "vision-clone",
        "qc_status": "pending"
      },
      "_source": "right"
    },
    {
      "id": "ASCE7-22-26.11.2.1-B7",
      "type": "body",
      "section": "26.11.2.1",
      "text": "The summations are over the height of the building, where hi is the height above grade of level i , and Li is the building length at level i parallel to the wind direction.",
      "cross_references": [],
      "bbox": {
        "x_start": 0.06,
        "x_end": 0.48,
        "y_start": 0.47,
        "y_end": 0.5
      },
      "column": "left",
      "metadata": {
        "extracted_by": "vision-clone",
        "qc_status": "pending"
      },
      "_source": "left"
    },
    {
      "id": "ASCE7-22-26.11-formula1",
      "type": "formula",
      "section": "26.11",
      "text": "For z < 15 ft\nKz = 2.41 (15/zg)^{2/α}\nFor z < 4.6 m\nKz = 2.41 (4.6/zg)^{2/α}\nFor 15 ft (4.6 m) ≤ z ≤ zg\nKz = 2.41 (z/zg)^{2/α}\nFor z > ≤ 3,280 ft (1,000 m)\nKz = 2.41",
      "cross_references": [],
      "bbox": {
        "x_start": 0.532,
        "x_end": 0.938,
        "y_start": 0.488,
        "y_end": 0.575
      },
      "column": "right",
      "expression": "K_z = 2.41 \\left(\\frac{z}{z_g}\\right)^{2/\\alpha}",
      "parameters": [
        "K_z = velocity pressure exposure coefficient",
        "z = height above ground level",
        "z_g = gradient height from Table 26.11-1",
        "\\alpha = power law exponent from Table 26.11-1"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "extracted_by": "vision-clone",
        "qc_status": "pending"
      },
      "_source": "right"
    },
    {
      "id": "ASCE7-22-26.11.3-H5",
      "type": "body",
      "section": "26.11.3",
      "text": "26.11.3 Approximate Natural Frequency The approximate lower bound natural frequency ( na ), in Hz, of concrete or structural steel buildings meeting the conditions of",
      "cross_references": [],
      "bbox": {
        "x_start": 0.06,
        "x_end": 0.48,
        "y_start": 0.51,
        "y_end": 0.56
      },
      "column": "left",
      "heading": true,
      "metadata": {
        "extracted_by": "vision-clone",
        "qc_status": "pending"
      },
      "_source": "left"
    },
    {
      "id": "ASCE7-22-26.11.3-H5-body",
      "type": "body",
      "section": "26.11.3",
      "text": "approximate lower bound natural frequency (na), in Hz, of concrete or structural steel buildings meeting the conditions of Section 26.11.2.1 is permitted to be determined from one of the following equations. For structural steel moment-resisting frame buildings,",
      "cross_references": [
        "26.11.2.1"
      ],
      "bbox": {
        "x_start": 0.06,
        "x_end": 0.48,
        "y_start": 0.52,
        "y_end": 0.56
      },
      "column": "left",
      "metadata": {
        "extracted_by": "vision-clone",
        "qc_status": "pending"
      },
      "_source": "left"
    },
    {
      "id": "ASCE7-22-26.11.3-F4",
      "type": "formula",
      "section": "26.11.3",
      "text": "na = 22.2/h^0.8",
      "cross_references": [],
      "bbox": {
        "x_start": 0.06,
        "x_end": 0.48,
        "y_start": 0.56,
        "y_end": 0.58
      },
      "column": "left",
      "expression": "n_a = \\frac{22.2}{h^{0.8}}",
      "parameters": [
        "n_a = approximate natural frequency in Hz",
        "h = height of structure in ft"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "extracted_by": "vision-clone",
        "qc_status": "pending"
      },
      "_source": "left"
    },
    {
      "id": "ASCE7-22-26.11-note1",
      "type": "body",
      "section": "26.11",
      "text": "2. α and zg are tabulated in Table 26.11-1.\n3. Linear interpolation for intermediate values of height z is acceptable.\n4. Exposure categories are defined in Section 26.7.",
      "cross_references": [
        "26.11-1",
        "26.7"
      ],
      "bbox": {
        "x_start": 0.532,
        "x_end": 0.938,
        "y_start": 0.575,
        "y_end": 0.608
      },
      "column": "right",
      "metadata": {
        "extracted_by": "vision-clone",
        "qc_status": "pending"
      },
      "_source": "right"
    },
    {
      "id": "ASCE7-22-26.11.3-F5",
      "type": "formula",
      "section": "26.11.3",
      "text": "na = 8.58/h^0.8",
      "cross_references": [],
      "bbox": {
        "x_start": 0.06,
        "x_end": 0.48,
        "y_start": 0.58,
        "y_end": 0.6
      },
